hpnicfProtocolVlan.name: hpnicfProtocolVlan

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module .

hpnicfProtocolVlan.description: This MIB contains the objects for managing the protocol-based VLAN configurations.

HpnicfvProtocolVlanProtocolType.name: HpnicfvProtocolVlanProtocolType
HpnicfvProtocolVlanProtocolType.description: Contains protocols both for Layer 3 and Layer 2.

HpnicfvProtocolVlanProtocolSubType.name: HpnicfvProtocolVlanProtocolSubType
HpnicfvProtocolVlanProtocolSubType.description: combine with HpnicfvProtocolVlanProtocolType. ethernetii(2), llc(3), raw(4), snap(5) are used when the value of HpnicfvProtocolVlanProtocolType is for Layer 3 protocols. etype(6) is used when the value of HpnicfvProtocolVlanProtocolType is for Layer 2 protocols. For detailed information, see the DESCRIPTION part of hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolTypeValue.

hpnicfProtocolNumAllVlan.name: hpnicfProtocolNumAllVlan
hpnicfProtocolNumAllVlan.description: The maximum number of protocols that can be configured on all VLANs. This number may vary with products.

hpnicfProtocolNumPerVlan.name: hpnicfProtocolNumPerVlan
hpnicfProtocolNumPerVlan.description: The maximum number of protocols that can be configured per VLAN. This number may vary with products.

hpnicfProtocolNumAllPort.name: hpnicfProtocolNumAllPort
hpnicfProtocolNumAllPort.description: The maximum number of protocols that can be applied on all ports. This number may vary with products.

hpnicfProtocolNumPerPort.name: hpnicfProtocolNumPerPort
hpnicfProtocolNumPerPort.description: The maximum number of protocols that can be applied to each port. This number may vary with products.

hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolIndex.name: hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolIndex
hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolIndex.description: The protocol index value of a row in this table is in the range of [0..hpnicfProtocolNumPerVlan-1]. This object may not be provided during creation. In this case, a number is assigned by system automatically.

hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolType.name: hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolType
hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolType.description: Specify protocol types supported by a protocol-based VLAN. Now protocols supported on Layer 3 include ip, ipx, at, ipv6, etc. Now protocols supported on Layer 2 include llc, snap, ethernetii, etc. For detailed information, see description of hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolTypeValue.

hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolTypeValue.name: hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolTypeValue
hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolTypeValue.description: The value of the configured protocol type. By default, semicolon(;) is used as a separator between different parts in the content of the object. The relationship among hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolType, hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolSubType and hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolTypeValue is as follows: |----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| | hpnicfProtocolVlan- | hpnicfProtocolVlan- | hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolTypeValue | | ProtocolType | ProtocolSubType | | |-------------------|-------------------|------------------------------------------------------| | ip | notused | notused for create operation | |-------------------|-------------------|------------------------------------------------------| | ipv6 | notused | notused for create operation | |-------------------|-------------------|------------------------------------------------------| | at | notused | notused for create operation | |-------------------|-------------------|------------------------------------------------------| | ipx | ethernetii | notused for create operation | | llc | | | | raw | | | | snap | | |-------------------|-------------------|------------------------------------------------------| | mode-snap | etype | hex string like '600', which means 0x0600. | | | | The range is [0x600..0xffff] | |-------------------|-------------------|------------------------------------------------------| | mode-ethernetii | etype | hex string like '600', which means 0x0600. | | | | The range is [0x600..0xffff] | |-------------------|-------------------|------------------------------------------------------| | mode-llc | notused | the sequence of different parts is as follows. | | | | [dsap value][;ssap value][dsap value;ssap value] | | | | Both range is [0x00..0xff] | | | | | | | | For example. Suppose value of dsap and ssap are 0x09 | | | | and 0x0a. | | | | If neither dsap or ssap, the string length is zero. | | | | If dsap provided, the string is '09;' or '09' | | | | If ssap provided, the value is ';0a' | | | | If dsap and ssap provided, the value is '09;0a' | |-------------------|-------------------|------------------------------------------------------|

hpnicfProtocolVlanRowStatus.name: hpnicfProtocolVlanRowStatus
hpnicfProtocolVlanRowStatus.description: The row status of this table.

hpnicfProtocolVlanPortIndex.name: hpnicfProtocolVlanPortIndex
hpnicfProtocolVlanPortIndex.description: The maximum number is the total number of ports supported by device.

hpnicfProtocolVlanPortRowStatus.name: hpnicfProtocolVlanPortRowStatus
hpnicfProtocolVlanPortRowStatus.description: The row status of this table.

hpnicfProtocolVlanPortStatus.name: hpnicfProtocolVlanPortStatus
hpnicfProtocolVlanPortStatus.description: The protocol VLAN status on the port. The value is active only when hpnicfProtocolVlanPortProtocolId has the corresponding entry in hpnicfProtocolVlanTable, the port link type is hybrid, and the VLAN is allowed by the port. active: protocol VLAN has been applied on the port. inactive: protocol VLAN is not applied on the port.

hpnicfDifferentProtocolNumAllPort.name: hpnicfDifferentProtocolNumAllPort
hpnicfDifferentProtocolNumAllPort.description: The maximum number of different protocols that can be applied to all ports.

hpnicfProtocolVlanCompliance.name: hpnicfProtocolVlanCompliance
hpnicfProtocolVlanCompliance.description: The compliance statement for protocol VLAN MIB.

hpnicfProtocolVlanOperateGroup.name: hpnicfProtocolVlanOperateGroup
hpnicfProtocolVlanOperateGroup.description: A group of scalar objects describing the maximum number.

hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolGroup.name: hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolGroup
hpnicfProtocolVlanProtocolGroup.description: A group of protocol VLAN protocol.

hpnicfProtocolVlanPortGroup.name: hpnicfProtocolVlanPortGroup
hpnicfProtocolVlanPortGroup.description: A group of protocol VLAN port.
